First Read: 20-Jan-26
HJR39 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 COMMENDING THE GENERAL FEDERATION OF WOMEN'S CLUBS ALABAMA
4 AND ITS PRESIDENT BECKY VANSANT.
5
6 WHEREAS, highest commendations and congratulations
7 are herein proudly presented to the General Federation of
8 Women's Clubs (GFWC) Alabama and its president, Becky
9 Vansant, as she concludes her 2024-2026 administration; and
10 WHEREAS, organized in 1895, GFWC Alabama was
11 chartered into the international organization General
12 Federation of Women's Clubs in 1907; for 131 years, GFWC
13 Alabama has worked to address the most pressing needs of our
14 communities, state, nation, and world; and
15 WHEREAS, The 50 clubs and 1,200 members located in
16 communities throughout Alabama develop outstanding programs
17 and projects to address common issues and concerns; and
18 WHEREAS, some areas addressed through programs and
19 projects include access to and support of the arts,
20 education and libraries, natural resource preservation,
21 veterans, public and individual health and wellness, child
22 advocacy, and citizenship; and
23 WHEREAS, the establishment of scholarships and
24 libraries has been a major focus area for GFWC Alabama and
25 local clubs; GFWC Alabama has been actively involved in the
26 GFWC's signature program, Domestic and Sexual Violence
27 Awareness and Prevention; and
28 WHEREAS, GFWC Alabama is an organization made up of
Page 1

WHEREAS, GFWC Alabama is an organization made up of
HJR39 Enrolled
29 women from all walks of life and across generations who have
30 a common goal of enhancing the lives of others through
31 volunteer service; as a part of this organization, members
32 grow in their understanding of issues and are enriched
33 through their service, further developing their talents and
34 skills while establishing lifelong connections; and
35 WHEREAS, the theme for the 2024-2026 administration
36 is "Living the Volunteer Spirit – Compassion in Action";
37 Becky Vansant's special project as GFWC Alabama's President
38 is "Mental Health Matters" which focuses on increasing
39 awareness about mental health concerns and striving to end
40 the stigma associated with mental health illness while
41 promoting the resources available in local communities,
42 state, and the nation; and
43 WHEREAS, the 131st Annual Convention of the GFWC
44 Alabama Federation of Women's Clubs is being held April
45 24-26, 2026, at the Montgomery Marriott Prattville Hotel and
46 Conference Center at Capitol Hill; members will discuss
47 common concerns, hear from experts in their fields, and
48 conduct the business necessary to allow this organization to
49 continue its 131-year legacy of enhancing the lives of
50 others; now therefore,
51 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
52 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That we highly commend and honor
53 the General Federation of Women's Clubs Alabama and its
54 members for the time, talent, and resources they have
55 committed to the service of others.
